## 3. Recovery objectives — RPO & RTO (owner-input)

<!-- guidance: RPO = maximum tolerable data loss (how far back the last good
backup is); RTO = maximum tolerable time to restore service. State the COMMITTED
target AND how the design supports it (continuous WAL → low RPO; warm standby →
low RTO). A target with no mechanism behind it is aspirational; reviewers want
the mechanism. If targets differ per datastore, give a row each. -->

| Objective | Target | How the design supports it | Evidence |
|---|---|---|---|
| **RPO** (max data loss) | {{RPO_TARGET}} | {{RPO_MECHANISM}} | {{RPO_EVIDENCE}} |
| **RTO** (max time to recover) | {{RTO_TARGET}} | {{RTO_MECHANISM}} | {{RTO_EVIDENCE}} |

{{RPO_RTO_NOTES}}

